      "Bash(this all of it?\" question — the bar updates live as filters, scrubbers\nand selections change, with a contextual hint slot \\(\"123 geolocated\",\n\"Loading device tracks\", \"Server reports 8497 — 2103 after dedupe\"\\).\n\nArchitecture: a CellebriteStatusProvider wraps all tabs in\nCellebriteView. Each tab calls useCellebriteStatus\\({ isActive, total,\ndisplayed, selected, label, hint }\\) — the active tab publishes; hidden\ntabs are gated so they don''t clobber the visible one. CellebriteStatusBar\nmounts once at the bottom of the shell and renders whatever the active\ntab last published, with a muted \"—\" before the first publish.\n\nWired into Overview, Comms Center and Events Center as the high-traffic\nsurfaces. Other Cellebrite tabs can adopt the hook later — the bar\ngracefully shows muted dashes until they do.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n\\)\")",
      "Bash(tile → right rail with the rows it contains\" UX.\n\nBoth honour the same case_id / report_keys / start_date / end_date\nfilter contract every other Cellebrite endpoint uses, plus an\noptional bbox on the tiles call so panning the map only aggregates\nthe visible area. Uses the case_id and \\(case_id,\ncellebrite_report_key\\) indexes shipped in fbe8df0 — no extra schema.\n\nFrontend helpers added to cellebriteEventsAPI but no UI consumer\nyet; the Locations tab continues to use raw-point rendering. The\ntab will switch to tiles in the next commit \\(G3\\) along with the\nrail integration.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n\\)\")",
      "mcp__Claude_in_Chrome__read_network_requests",
      "mcp__Claude_in_Chrome__read_console_messages",
      "Bash(slow\" reports without re-deriving the diagnostic flow each time.\n\nFive tiers, run in order, measure-first posture:\n\n  Tier 0 — verify deploy state \\(HEAD commit, services up, free,\n           df, journal for OOM/tracebacks\\)\n  Tier 1 — identify the slow request \\(browser network tab or\n           server-side curl -w timings against the case-id\\)\n  Tier 2 — narrow to layer \\(Python projection vs Neo4j Cypher\n           vs JSON serialise/transit\\), with EXPLAIN/PROFILE Cypher\n           commands and SHOW INDEXES for index-coverage check\n  Tier 3 — memory-pressure diagnostics \\(dmesg OOM, ps RSS, watch\n           backend RSS over time during repro\\)\n  Tier 4 — Cellebrite-specific quick checks \\(reconciliation,\n           geocoder status, per-phone event counts\\)\n  Tier 5 — escalation rules: when to STOP and report rather than\n           silently restart / bump a limit\n\nIncludes a Phase A–D commit map so the on-box Claude doesn''t\nmis-attribute slowness to features it didn''t cause. None of the\nshipped tab-scoped endpoints run on case open after d9b0e91, so\n\"case is slow on open\" should not blame them without proof.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n\\)\")",
      "Bash(hard to work in\" because the conversation timeline at the bottom and\nthe From/To filter at the top kept it squeezed.\n\nReusable shared/ResizableSplit primitive:\n- 6px draggable divider with hover affordance + grab cursor\n- pointermove/up live on document so the drag tracks even when the\n  cursor leaves the divider\n- Per-case localStorage persistence \\(keys like cb.comms.bottomTimeline.{caseId}\\)\n  so investigators get their preferred ratio back next session\n- Vertical or horizontal direction; min/max bounds enforced\n\nApplied to:\n- Comms Center: thread-list / thread-view horizontal split + the\n  cross-type timeline at the bottom is now drag-resizable upward,\n  giving the message feed as much vertical room as the user wants\n- Locations: map / table vertical split \\(was fixed h-64 table\\)\n- Events Center: map / table vertical split for the ''split'' viewMode\n\nPlan file extended with Phase H \\(section 12\\) covering primitive design,\nper-tab application, and what we deferred \\(horizontal splits in\nLocations, named layout presets, drag-to-fully-collapse\\).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n\\)\")",
